The reason why I could not move the rigid body was a simple C++ mistake. Instead of getting a reference to the members X, V, theta and omega, I got a copy which was updated, but lost its value between two calls of stepscene():

Wrong:

Vector2s x = rbs[i].getX();

Correct:

Vector2s& x = rbs[i].getX();

After fixing this and executing the typical Euler update equations (4: don't forget theta and omega), I finally managed to get all inertia Tests done.
